      "content": "Do not give him your adult ibuprofen, even a small amount, as mixing medications without professional guidance is dangerous. You should use children's ibuprofen, dosed correctly according to his weight, if you need a second medication. For the cough, try using a humidifier in his room and ensuring he stays well-hydrated. If the cough is severe, a good dose of children's liquid decongestant, if approved by your doctor, can help.",
